Defendant Christopher L Williams in court, in custody, with attorney J A Rosario.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
State filed an Amended Information.  Plea agreement placed on the record. 
  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Counts 1 and 2 of the amended information.  Court finds defendant guilty.
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:
COUNT 1:
IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS HUBER, w/Standard Release Conditions (CREDIT - 45 days);

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS, concurrent with count 2. 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No violent contact with Brandy A. or any family member.
*Domestic Violence Counseling through a State certified batterers intervention program.
*Psychological evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

RESTITUTION:  To be determined.  (District Attorney's office to turn over any restitution documentation to Attorney Rosario within 30 days and copy the court.  Attorney Rosario has 1 week after the receipt of the documation to notify the court in writing whether there is a stipulation or a hearing is to be set.  Otherwise, the court will grant the restitution request and amend the Judgment of Conviction).

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
